      "path": "server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go",
      "function": "rangeKeys"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The authoritative source of the 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' error originates in the etcd-io/etcd repository, NOT the vendored copies in kubernetes/kubernetes. The error constant ErrCompacted is defined in server/mvcc/kvstore.go (line 39) with the exact error message. The core function rangeKeys, implemented in server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go (starting at line 128), is responsible for handling range queries against the MVCC (Multi-Version Concurrency Control) storage engine. When a client requests data at a revision that has been garbage-collected by compaction, the rangeKeys function checks if the requested revision is less than the store's compact main revision (line 136). If it is, the function immediately returns the ErrCompacted error (line 137), which is then wrapped as an OutOfRange gRPC error by the error-mapping layer. The Kubernetes vendored copies in vendor/go.etcd.io/etcd/server/v3/mvcc/kvstore.go are NOT authoritative - they are snapshots from a specific etcd version vendored into Kubernetes at a point in time, and bug fixes and updates in upstream etcd would not be reflected in those vendor copies. Similarly, the Kubernetes error-mapping layer at staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/errors.go only translates the etcd error into Kubernetes error types; it is not the source of the original error definition."
}

